    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Initially, \"fake news\" was often used to dismiss baseless partisan attacks or sensationalist reporting, suggesting it was manufactured falsehoods. Over the last decade, the term has become more broadly weaponized, frequently used by political actors to delegitimize legitimate critical journalism or opposing viewpoints. This shift has turned it into a catch-all label for anything deemed inconvenient by the speaker. Consequently, its usage has become heavily polarized, moving beyond simple factual inaccuracy to become an ideological weapon.",
